# <PROJECT_NAME> — human setup checklist

These are the **irreducibly human** tasks — external accounts, store/dashboard
config, signing, secrets, and legal — that Claude cannot do for you. Everything
else (all code, and all simulator verification against the local Firebase
emulators) is automated.

The app **builds and is fully verified on simulators against the local Firebase
Emulator Suite** — the `dev` flavor uses a `demo-*` project ID, which the
emulators treat as offline-only, so **no real Firebase project is needed during
development**. Most of this is needed only for the **Backend integration pass**
plan step, the real (`prod`) build, and real-device smoke tests. Front-load the
slow ones (Apple enrollment, store IAP products, RevenueCat) — they gate later
release work.

Items that don't apply should be struck through: `- [x] ~~item~~ _(not needed)_`

## Toolchain (one-time per machine)

- [ ] Flutter SDK installed (`flutter doctor` green).
- [ ] Java 11+ installed (`java -version`) — the Firebase Emulator Suite needs it.
- [ ] Firebase CLI installed: `npm install -g firebase-tools` (or
      `curl -sL https://firebase.tools | bash`).
- [ ] `claude` CLI installed and `claude login` done.
- [ ] Dart MCP registered: `claude mcp add dart -- dart mcp-server`
- [ ] Claude Code restarted; `claude mcp list` shows dart Connected.

## Git & repository

- [ ] Repo detached from the bundle: either `rm -rf .git && git init`, or
      `git remote set-url origin <your-repo>`.
- [ ] Your own remote created and `git remote -v` shows it.

> The autobuild runner refuses to push while `origin` still points at
> `flutter-app-bundle` — it downgrades push to off and tells you.

## Firebase (if using Firebase)

Development needs **no real project** — the `dev` flavor runs against the local
Emulator Suite with a `demo-<app>` project ID (offline-only). The items below
are needed **before the "Backend integration pass" plan step** and release:

- [ ] **Staging** Firebase project created. Project ID: ___________________
- [ ] **Production** Firebase project created. Project ID: ___________________
      — never smoke-test against production.
- [ ] `firebase login` done.
- [ ] `flutterfire configure --project=<staging-id>` run; `firebase_options.dart`
      generated.
- [ ] Sign-in providers enabled on **staging** (Email, Google, Apple — as needed).

> Security rules and indexes (`firestore.rules`, `firestore.indexes.json`)
> already live in the repo and are exercised by the emulator continuously;
> deploying them to staging happens in the backend-pass step itself.

## Monetization — RevenueCat + store products (if paid)

- [ ] RevenueCat account created; project + public SDK API keys obtained.
- [ ] API keys provided to the app via `--dart-define` / CI secret (not committed).
- [ ] **App Store Connect:** subscription/IAP products created (IDs match the
      spec); pricing, localizations, and agreements/tax/banking completed.
- [ ] **Google Play Console:** matching products created; pricing set.
- [ ] RevenueCat entitlement + offerings configured; products linked to both stores.
- [ ] `ios/Configuration.storekit` product IDs match the store products (for
      simulator purchase testing).
- [ ] Sandbox/license test accounts added; real-device purchase + **restore**
      verified.

## Apple Developer (if shipping to iOS)

- [ ] Apple Developer Program enrolled.
- [ ] App ID created with bundle ID.
- [ ] Xcode auto-signing configured (Runner → Signing & Capabilities → select team).

## Android signing (if shipping to Play Store)

- [ ] Release keystore generated.
- [ ] `android/key.properties` created.
- [ ] SHA fingerprints added to Firebase project.

## Autobuild runner (optional — unattended builds)

Only needed if you want Claude to implement the whole plan on its own with
`runner/autobuild.py` (instead of running `/step` yourself). See `docs/autobuild.md`.

- [ ] Python 3.10+ available (`python3 --version`).
- [ ] **Create & activate a virtual environment, then install the SDK:**
  ```bash
  python3 -m venv runner/.venv
  source runner/.venv/bin/activate        # Windows: runner\.venv\Scripts\activate
  pip install -r runner/requirements.txt  # installs claude-agent-sdk
  ```
- [ ] Claude Code CLI installed + authenticated (`claude login`) — the SDK spawns it.
- [ ] Java + firebase CLI installed (agents start the emulators).
- [ ] An iOS simulator can boot (the runner drives it).
- [ ] (Only if a step configures real Firebase) service-account key exported:
      `export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/sa.json`
- [ ] Smoke-test the wiring before a real run (no commits, leaves changes in tree):
  ```bash
  runner/.venv/bin/python runner/autobuild.py --dry-run
  ```

